'''John Francis "Red" Flaherty''' (April 25, 1917 - April 1, 1999) was a professional [[baseball]] [[umpire (baseball)|umpire]] who worked in the [[American League]] from 1953 to 1973. Flaherty umpired 3,208 [[Major League Baseball|major league]] games in his 21 year career. He umpired in four [[World Series]] ([[1955 World Series|1955]], [[1958 World Series|1958]], [[1965 World Series|1965]], and [[1970 World Series|1970]]), two [[League Championship Series]] ([[1969 American League Championship Series|1969]] and [[1972 American League Championship Series|1972]]) and three [[Major League Baseball All-Star Game|All-Star Games]] ([[1956 Major League Baseball All-Star Game|1956]], [[1961 Major League Baseball All-Star Game (second game)|1961]] and [[1969 Major League Baseball All-Star Game|1969]]). <ref>[http://www.retrosheet.org/boxesetc/F/Pflahr901.htm Retrosheet]</ref> 

==Death==
Flaherty died on April 1, 1999 at his home in Falmouth, MA. His death resulted from stroke-related complications.<ref>{{Citation
